<TITLE> Sulphur fumes kill four in Italian work accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bari, Italy, March 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Four workers were killed on Monday when they breathed in toxic sulphur fumes from the tank of a truck near the southern Italian city of Bari, police said. The local police said a worker was overcome by the fumes while cleaning the inside of the tank. Three other workers died when they entered the tank to help him, and a fifth worker is in a critical condition. The high number of workplace deaths is considered by many to be a national scandal in Italy, where recent draft government legislation aimed at tightening safety conditions has not been approved by parliament
